sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BB base ve
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: BioBrick base vector (for constructing pSB**5 vectors)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is a vector scaffold for constructing new BioBricks vectors. Information on the design is available at http://openwetware.org/wiki/Synthetic_Biology:Vectors/pSB%2A%2A5_design
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This is a composite part generated from several basic parts obtained from a variety of sources.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Documented at http://openwetware.org/wiki/Synthetic_Biology:Vectors/pSB%2A%2A5_design
Due to technical difficulties during synthesis, rather than including BBa_P1011 as designed, BBa_P1016 was synthesized as a component of this part. Hence, BBa_I51000 documents the original design and BBa_I51001 is the vector scaffold as synthesized. BBa_I52002 is the base vector as corrected from the synthesized construct.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: TOPO
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Insertion of this site will enable generation of a TOPO vector. The vector will have a T overhang and permit binding of topoisomerase I for direct cloning of PCR products. See http://openwetware.org/wiki/Topoisomerase_I_mediated_TA_cloning for a complete description of Topoisomerase I mediated cloning.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: TSS
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part contains a stop codon in all 6 reading frames. Useful for ensuring that translation does not proceed through this part.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0055
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Terminator to be placed upstream of multiple cloning site in new pSB series plasmids.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: VF2
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Forward primer for sequencing/amplifying BioBrick parts (VF2)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Originally named VF2, primer binds upstream of the standard BBa_MCS on biobrick vectors.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Tom Knight

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0053
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Terminator from the E.coli His operon
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Caitlin Conboy

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: NheI
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: NheI restriction enzyme site (XbaI, SpeI compatible overhang)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: NheI recognition site. Digestion with NheI generates a compatible cohesive end to XbaI and SpeI.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: ampR
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This contains TetR, a terminator and then AmpR and a terminator
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: NheI
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: NheI restriction enzyme site (XbaI, SpeI compatible overhang)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: NheI recognition site. Digestion with NheI generates a compatible cohesive end to XbaI and SpeI.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0062
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Reverse of B0052, E.coli transcriptional terminator from the ribosomal RNA rrnC operon.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Caitlin Conboy

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: VR
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Reverse BioBrick primer annealing site (VR binding site)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the VR sequence to be used in construction of plasmids which include the VR primer site. It is the reverse complement of BBa_G00101.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0054
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Terminator to be placed downstream of multiple cloning site in new pSB series plasmids. Similar to BBa_B0051.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:SequenceAnnotation.dcterms:title: identical to E. coli MG1655 between tonB and yciA

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: TSS
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part contains a stop codon in all 6 reading frames. Useful for ensuring that translation does not proceed through this part.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: TOPO
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Insertion of this site will enable generation of a TOPO vector. The vector will have a T overhang and permit binding of topoisomerase I for direct cloning of PCR products. See http://openwetware.org/wiki/Topoisomerase_I_mediated_TA_cloning for a complete description of Topoisomerase I mediated cloning. This site belongs 3' of the cloning site. It is the reverse complement of BBa_B0043.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: Suffix
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part is the standard BioBricks suffix.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: Prefix
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part is the standard BioBricks prefix.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: ccdB
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part is a differs from BBa_P1011 in that the mutations introduced in BBa_P1011 to remove restriction sites are not present in this part. It does have the "normal" ccd promoter and ccdB coding region. It also has a double TAA stop codon as per BioBrick conventions.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This part is derived from BBa_P1010 but it lacks ccdA-.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: ccdA- was eliminated since it is an inactive form of ccdA and should not be required for the toxic phenotype of ccdB.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: pUC19 ori
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Minimal pUC19-derived high copy replication origin
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: High copy origin of replication derived from pSB1A3. Designed to omit antibiotic resistance markers and primer binding sites. Lacks mutations that render BBa_I50020 nonfunctional as a replication origin.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: We had to leave several restriction sites in because point mutations that eliminated these sites were found to render the origin nonfunctional.
